#       Cloud Music - playlist/album/radio downloader) — a Node.js
#       CLI for downloading audio tracks from NetEase Cloud Music
#       (网易云音乐), the dominant streaming service in China.
#       Distinguishing from youtube-dl, yt-dlp, spotdl, and other
#       music downloaders by:
#         - NETEASE CLOUD MUSIC FOCUS: targets music.163.com URLs
#           for playlists / albums / radio programs / DJ radio /
#           personal-favorites lists; uses NetEase's internal API
#           via session cookies
#         - URL OR ID INPUT: accepts either full URL
#           (https://music.163.com/#/playlist?id=XXX) OR bare
#           playlist ID
#         - 4 QUALITY TIERS: --quality 128/192/320/999 (kbps)
#           with 999 = max available
#         - TEMPLATED FILENAMES: --format ":name/:singer - :songName
#           .:ext" — supports :name (playlist) / :singer / :songName
#           / :ext / :programDate / :programOrder placeholders
#         - DUAL FORMAT DEFAULTS: detects "radio" / "djradio" in URL
#           and switches default --format to include :programDate +
#           :programOrder for DJ radio programs
#         - SKIP-IF-EXISTS via --skip (default true): existing files
#           of acceptable size are skipped, enabling resume behavior
#         - RETRY POLICY: --retry-times (default 3) + --retry-
#           timeout (default 3 mins) for transient API failures
#         - PROGRESS BARS via --progress (default true)
#         - .yunrc FILE: rc-factory loads ~/.yunrc / .yunrc for
#           default flag values
#         - COOKIE AUTH: reads ~/.config/yun/cookie.txt for
#           NetEase session cookies (required for VIP-only tracks)
#         - HUMANIZED OUTPUT: every duration / time-remaining /
#           ETA is formatted via vercel/ms + humanize-duration
#           for "1h 30m" / "5min" style strings
#       Used by: NetEase Cloud Music subscribers wanting offline
#       copies of their playlists, DJ radio archivers, music
#       collectors building local libraries from streaming
